</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="394" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[674,1210,913,1224]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">
<taxonomicName authority="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati, 2012" authorityName="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati" authorityYear="2012" box="[677,869,944,970]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyclochlamydidae" genus="Cyclochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aperta" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[677,869,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Cyclochlamys aperta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[873,927,945,971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically closest to 
<taxonomicName authority="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati, 2010" authorityName="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati" authorityYear="2010" box="[674,1203,976,1002]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyclochlamydidae" genus="Cyclochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="australense">
<emphasis box="[674,915,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Cyclochlamys australense</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="DIJKSTRA H. H. &amp; MAESTRATI P." box="[920,1203,976,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" pagination="333 - 358" refId="ref21878" refString="DIJKSTRA H. H. &amp; MAESTRATI P. 2010. - Pectinoidea (Mollusca, Bivalvia, Propeamussiidae, Entoliidae and Pectinidae) from the Austral Islands (French Polynesia). Zoosystema 32 (2): 333 - 358. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2010 n 2 a 6" type="journal article" year="2010">Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Austral Islands (lives in 
<quantity box="[992,1069,1008,1035]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="5.2" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" unit="m" value="27.5" valueMax="52.0" valueMin="3.0">3-52 m</quantity>
).Both species are almost the same size (
<taxonomicName authority="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati, 2012" authorityName="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati" authorityYear="2012" box="[935,1029,1040,1066]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyclochlamydidae" genus="Cyclochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aperta" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[935,1029,1040,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">C. aperta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1035,1091,1040,1066]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<quantity box="[1096,1180,1040,1066]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
in height, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati" authorityYear="2010" box="[757,898,1071,1098]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyclochlamydidae" genus="Cyclochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="australense">
<emphasis box="[757,898,1071,1098]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">C. australense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<quantity box="[904,993,1071,1098]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 mm</quantity>
), and are posteriorly oblique. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati, 2012" authorityName="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati" authorityYear="2012" box="[873,967,1103,1129]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyclochlamydidae" genus="Cyclochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aperta" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[873,967,1103,1129]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">C. aperta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[972,1028,1103,1129]" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is almost smooth with only a few very weak commarginal growth lines. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dijkstra &amp; Maestrati" authorityYear="2010" box="[741,995,1166,1192]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cyclochlamydidae" genus="Cyclochlamys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pectinida" pageId="5" pageNumber="394" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="australense">
<emphasis box="[741,995,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="394">Cyclochlamys australense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a commarginal vesicular sculpture in late growth stage.
</paragraph>
